commit.message: update ChangeLog
allow to choose binary installation path at configure step
fix project name in CMakeLists.txt file
added man page installation to CMakeLists.txt
+ man page
doc/inside.md added, with description of some internals
update ChangeLog for v0.2.1
explicitly state license terms. GPLv3
updating README.md
rename binary to `reiserfs-defrag' and add install target
extract unique elements from file list supplied
use local variable instead of param.firstobjs
do not try to move sparse blocks in moveObjectsUp
fix small signed/unsiged issue
update ChangeLog

protect sealed files from incremental algorithm

(sealed_objs)
use AG sealing in moveObjectsUp

implement AG sealing

sealing means that AG will not be freed or sweeped out
Defrag::moveObjectsUp now return success status
allow interruption of "move up"
progress bars for "move up" feature
made moveObjectsUp work

fix minor bug in ReiserFs::recursivelyGetBlocksOfObject

that prevented correct defragmentation of files larger than
`limit' blocks. (stopped enumeration too early sometimes).

changed first parameter of (setI|i)ndirectItemRef to item_header

that enforces type checking and thus eliminates possible errors

pass whole item_header to dirHeader and dirEntryName (as first param)

to make parameter order consistent with indirectItemRef

fixed Block::dirEntryName

names that have length multiple of 8 are packed without zero terminators
so one need to check previous dir entry position to determine name end.
implemetation of file moving to the fs beginning
added const variant of [] operator for ag_entry struct
+ FsBitmap::AGFreeBlockCount
command-line parameter for block cache size setting
